      "description": "Principles: DRY knowledge, Localize change, Make bugs hard to write.\n\nEvidence:\n- path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts:189-195 :: runtime defines a local `isRecord` helper.\n- path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/temp.ts:54-68 :: temp defines both `isRecord` and `parsePositiveInteger` again.\n- path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/shared.ts:55-78 :: results/shared exports another `isRecord` plus another `parsePositiveInteger`.\n- workflow: rg -n \"function isRecord|function parsePositiveInteger\" extensions/agent-browser/lib :: found duplicate implementations in runtime.ts, temp.ts, and results/shared.ts.\n\nWhy it matters: these helpers sit on boundary parsing for session state, temp-budget env vars, and result rendering. Any future adjustment to what counts as a record or how numeric env values are normalized has to be synchronized manually across multiple modules.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: extract the truly shared helpers to one small common module and import them where needed, while keeping higher-level module boundaries intact.\n\nAcceptance criteria: `isRecord` and `parsePositiveInteger` each have a single canonical implementation; affected modules import that implementation; `npm run verify` and `npm run verify:package` both pass afterward.",
      "priority": "medium",
